cards.name: Alakazam
cards.flavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5000.

cards.name: Blastoise
cards.flavorText: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

cards.name: Chansey
cards.flavorText: A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch it.

cards.name: Charizard
cards.flavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to unintentionally cause forest fires.

cards.name: Clefairy
cards.flavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

cards.name: Gyarados
cards.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

cards.name: Hitmonchan
cards.flavorText: While seeming to do nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

cards.name: Machamp
cards.flavorText: Using its amazing muscles, it throws powerful punches that can knock its victim clear over the horizon.

cards.name: Magneton
cards.flavorText: Formed by several Magnemites linked together. It frequently appears when sunspots flare up.

cards.name: Mewtwo
cards.flavorText: A scientist created this Pokémon after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

cards.name: Nidoking
cards.flavorText: Uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break its prey's bones.

cards.name: Ninetales
cards.flavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

cards.name: Poliwrath
cards.flavorText: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

cards.name: Raichu
cards.flavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

cards.name: Venusaur
cards.flavorText: This plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

cards.name: Zapdos
cards.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon said to appear from clouds while wielding enormous lightning bolts.

cards.name: Beedrill
cards.flavorText: Flies at high speed and attacks using the large, venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

cards.name: Dragonair
cards.flavorText: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

cards.name: Dugtrio
cards.flavorText: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

cards.name: Electabuzz
cards.flavorText: Normally found near power plants, it can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

cards.name: Electrode
cards.flavorText: It stores electrical energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

cards.name: Pidgeotto
cards.flavorText: Very protective of its sprawling territory, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

cards.name: Arcanine
cards.flavorText: A Pokémon that has been long admired for its beauty. It runs gracefully, as if on wings.

cards.name: Charmeleon
cards.flavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it raises the temperature to unbearably high levels.

cards.name: Dewgong
cards.flavorText: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

cards.name: Dratini
cards.flavorText: Long considered a mythical Pokémon until recently, when a small colony was found living underwater.

cards.name: Farfetch'd
cards.flavorText: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. This sprig is used much like a metal sword.

cards.name: Growlithe
cards.flavorText: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

cards.name: Haunter
cards.flavorText: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

cards.name: Ivysaur
cards.flavorText: When the bulb on its back grows large, the Pokémon seems to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

cards.name: Jynx
cards.flavorText: Merely by meditating, the Pokémon launches a powerful psychic energy attack.

cards.name: Kadabra
cards.flavorText: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches even to those just nearby.

cards.name: Kakuna
cards.flavorText: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

cards.name: Machoke
cards.flavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful that it must wear a power-save belt to help regulate its motions.

cards.name: Magikarp
cards.flavorText: In the distant past, it was stronger than its horribly weak descendants that exist today.

cards.name: Magmar
cards.flavorText: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

cards.name: Nidorino
cards.flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

cards.name: Poliwhirl
cards.flavorText: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

cards.name: Porygon
cards.flavorText: A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

cards.name: Raticate
cards.flavorText: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It seems to slow down if they are cut off.

cards.name: Seel
cards.flavorText: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. This horn is used for bashing through thick ice.

cards.name: Wartortle
cards.flavorText: Often hides in water to stalk unweary prey. When swimming quickly, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

cards.name: Abra
cards.flavorText: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and teleport to safety.

cards.name: Bulbasaur
cards.flavorText: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. Thus, a plant sprouted and now grows with this Pokémon.

cards.name: Caterpie
cards.flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

cards.name: Charmander
cards.flavorText: Obviously prefers hot places. If it gets caught in the rain, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

cards.name: Diglett
cards.flavorText: Lives about three feet underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

cards.name: Doduo
cards.flavorText: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

cards.name: Drowzee
cards.flavorText: Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

cards.name: Gastly
cards.flavorText: Almost invisible, this gaseous Pokémon cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

cards.name: Koffing
cards.flavorText: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

cards.name: Machop
cards.flavorText: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

cards.name: Magnemite
cards.flavorText: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses attacks like Thunder Wave.

cards.name: Metapod
cards.flavorText: It is vulnerable to attack because its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

cards.name: Nidoran ♂
cards.flavorText: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger, more powerful of its horns secretes venom.

cards.name: Onix
cards.flavorText: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, though colored black.

cards.name: Pidgey
cards.flavorText: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

cards.name: Pikachu
cards.flavorText: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can cause lightning storms.

cards.name: Poliwag
cards.flavorText: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming over trying to stand.

cards.name: Ponyta
cards.flavorText: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything flat in moments.

cards.name: Rattata
cards.flavorText: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

cards.name: Sandshrew
cards.flavorText: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

cards.name: Squirtle
cards.flavorText: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

cards.name: Starmie
cards.flavorText: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value this core as a gem.

cards.name: Staryu
cards.flavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

cards.name: Tangela
cards.flavorText: Its whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. These vines shake as it walks.

cards.name: Voltorb
cards.flavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Monster Ball, it has zapped many people.

cards.name: Vulpix
cards.flavorText: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. Its tail splits from the tip as it grows older.

cards.name: Weedle
cards.flavorText: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp, venomous stinger on its head.

cards.name: Clefable
cards.flavorText: A timid Fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

cards.name: Electrode
cards.flavorText: It stores electrical energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

cards.name: Flareon
cards.flavorText: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

cards.name: Jolteon
cards.flavorText: It accumulates negative ions from the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.

cards.name: Kangaskhan
cards.flavorText: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is three years old.

cards.name: Mr. Mime
cards.flavorText: If interrupted while miming, it will slap around the enemy with its broad hands.

cards.name: Nidoqueen
cards.flavorText: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

cards.name: Pidgeot
cards.flavorText: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

cards.name: Pinsir
cards.flavorText: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing its victim around and toss it hard.

cards.name: Scyther
cards.flavorText: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one of it.

cards.name: Snorlax
cards.flavorText: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

cards.name: Vaporeon
cards.flavorText: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin that is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

cards.name: Venomoth
cards.flavorText: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

cards.name: Victreebel
cards.flavorText: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

cards.name: Vileplume
cards.flavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

cards.name: Wigglytuff
cards.flavorText: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

cards.name: Clefable

cards.name: Wigglytuff
cards.flavorText: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

cards.name: Butterfree
cards.flavorText: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

cards.name: Dodrio
cards.flavorText: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

cards.name: Exeggutor
cards.flavorText: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an Exeggcute.

cards.name: Fearow
cards.flavorText: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

cards.name: Gloom
cards.flavorText: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool; it is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

cards.name: Lickitung
cards.flavorText: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a stinging sensation when it licks enemies.

cards.name: Marowak
cards.flavorText: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to K.O. targets.

cards.name: Nidorina
cards.flavorText: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

cards.name: Parasect
cards.flavorText: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

cards.name: Persian
cards.flavorText: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

cards.name: Primeape
cards.flavorText: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until its quarry is caught.

cards.name: Rapidash
cards.flavorText: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

cards.name: Rhydon
cards.flavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3600 degrees.

cards.name: Seaking
cards.flavorText: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

cards.name: Tauros
cards.flavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

cards.name: Weepinbell
cards.flavorText: It spits out poisonpowder to immobilize the enemy, and then finishes the enemy with a spray of acid.

cards.name: Bellsprout
cards.flavorText: A carniverous Pokémon that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

cards.name: Cubone
cards.flavorText: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this Pokémon's real face.

cards.name: Eevee
cards.flavorText: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from elemental stones.

cards.name: Exeggcute
cards.flavorText: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

cards.name: Goldeen
cards.flavorText: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname "Water Queen."

cards.name: Jigglypuff
cards.flavorText: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

cards.name: Mankey
cards.flavorText: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next.

cards.name: Meowth
cards.flavorText: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

cards.name: Nidoran ♀
cards.flavorText: Although small, its venomous barbs make this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

cards.name: Oddish
cards.flavorText: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

cards.name: Paras
cards.flavorText: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

cards.name: Pikachu
cards.flavorText: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.

cards.name: Rhyhorn
cards.flavorText: Its massive bones are 1,000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.

cards.name: Spearow
cards.flavorText: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speeds to stay airborne.

cards.name: Venonat
cards.flavorText: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.
